## CSS organization architecture

### What belongs where

`style.css` is the project design system. It contains:
- Tokens (§2 `:root`)
- Typography defaults — foundational only (§4)
- Wrapper and layout utilities (§5)
- Shared patterns: buttons, pill labels, eyebrows, title plates, gradient lines, card/glass panels (§10)
- Header and footer brand styles (§10g–10h)
- Contact drawer or global overlays if used (§10i)
- Page-scoped overrides using body.page-{slug} (§10)
- Small utilities (§10j)

Block CSS files contain ONLY what is unique to that block:
- Block grid and layout structure
- Variant behavior
- Block-specific responsive rules
- One-off positioning
- Block-specific exceptions — document with a comment

THE SHARED PATTERN RULE:
If the same visual treatment appears in more than one block,
promote it to style.css Section 10. Do NOT duplicate it across
multiple block CSS files.

### Block wrapper pattern

Every block must use an outer section and an inner .wrapper.
Variant and style classes belong on the outer section:

```html
<section class="block_name block_name_variant_[variant] block_name_style_[style]">
    <div class="wrapper block_name_wrapper">
        ...
    </div>
</section>
```

Outer section:       background, full-width, vertical spacing.
                     Variant and style classes live here.
.wrapper:            max-width, margin auto, horizontal padding.
                     Defined once in style.css §5a — reuse it.
Block wrapper class: block-specific layout only.

Rules:
- Do not redefine max-width, margin auto, or horizontal padding in block CSS
- Always use BOTH wrapper classes together: class="wrapper block_name_wrapper"
- Variant and style classes go on the outer section, never on the inner wrapper
- Variants change layout/styling/behavior — not wrapper geometry
  (unless there is a documented exception)

### Global element selector rule

Global element rules (h1–h6, p, a) in style.css §4 must stay
foundational: font-family, font-size, line-height, color, margin.
Decorative treatments — heading underlines, display overrides on
bare elements, complex pseudo-elements on bare selectors — belong
as opt-in classes or shared patterns in §10, not bare global rules.
If a project intentionally uses stronger global styling, document
that choice with a comment.

Full reference: Guides/STYLESHEET_GUIDE.md

### main layout — cleanup completed (May 2026)

`main` in style.css §5b was unconstrained as part of a coordinated
layout cleanup. It now has only margin: var(--space-16) 0 — no
max-width, no horizontal padding. All 15 blocks are migrated to the
outer section + inner .wrapper pattern and each block owns containment.

Breakout math is still present on Hero and CTA Banner full-width variants:

    width: 100vw;
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
    margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);

Still needed — not because main is constrained, but because
the_content() renders inside a .wrapper div in page.php. The
full-width outer section must escape that wrapper.

RULES:
- Do NOT remove the breakout math from Hero or CTA Banner — still required
- Do NOT add breakout math to other blocks — not the pattern for new work
- Ensure body or html has overflow-x: hidden — without it, 100vw can
  cause a few pixels of horizontal scroll on pages with a visible scrollbar

