## PHP conventions

```php
// Short echo tags — preferred
<?= $variable; ?>

// ACF field pattern
$title = get_field('field_name');
if ( $title ) : ?>
    <h2><?= $title; ?></h2>
<?php endif; ?>

// Always escape output
echo esc_html( $variable );
echo esc_url( $url );
echo esc_attr( $attribute );

// Repeater subfields
while ( have_rows('repeater_field') ) : the_row();
    $item = get_sub_field('sub_field_name');
endwhile;
```

---

## Block architecture

Every block follows the same 4-file pattern:

```
~wp_blocks/block-name/
├── block.json      ← Registration, metadata, ACF config
├── block-name.php  ← Render template, pulls ACF fields
├── block-name.css  ← Block styles using tokens only
└── block-name.js   ← Interactivity (only if needed)
```

All blocks are auto-registered via a glob loop in functions.php.

All 15 blocks use "category": "boilerplate-blocks" and appear under the "Boilerplate Blocks" group in the editor. Category registered via add_filter( 'block_categories_all' ) in functions.php.

### Block JS — loading patterns

Gallery, Accordion, and Video all load their JS from scripts.js — NOT via viewScript in block.json. A video.js file exists in the video block folder but is not wired up via block.json.

Why: all three depend on jQuery being loaded first. scripts.js declares jquery and owl-core-js as dependencies in functions.php, guaranteeing correct load order.

